sentences: Laura Kathryn Wright (born 17 June 1990) is an English soprano.
In April 2016, she performed at The Grand National and, in July, she was the official anthem singer at the British Grand Prix..
In 2016, she wrote “Heroes”; the first official anthem of the England Women's Cricket team.
2014: "Don't Give Up" (The Soundtrack of My Life)
Wright's first notable achievement, at 14, was as chorister of the year..
She has previously performed at men's and women’s rugby matches at Twickenham.
